NAME
       usermgmt - a simple user management system in a Unix environment

SYNOPSIS
       usermgmt

DESCRIPTION
       The usermgmt program provides a simple command-line interface for
       managing users and groups in a Unix-like environment. It allows users
       to add, delete, and modify user accounts, as well as manage user
       groups. The program interacts with the system using system commands.

COMMANDS
       The following commands are available in usermgmt:

       1. Add user
          Adds a new user to the system.

       2. Delete user
          Deletes an existing user from the system.

       3. Add group
          Adds a new group to the system.

       4. Delete group
          Deletes an existing group from the system.

       5. Change user info
          Allows users to modify user information, such as username, home
          directory, or shell.

       6. Change account info
          Allows users to modify account information, such as password,
          password expiration, or account expiration.

       7. Assign user to group
          Assigns a user to a specific group.

       8. List all users
          Lists all users currently registered on the system.

       9. List all groups
          Lists all groups currently available on the system.

       10. Exit
           Exits the usermgmt program.

EXAMPLES
       To add a new user, run:
           usermgmt
           Enter your choice: 1
           Enter username: newuser

